166inline int64_t CpRandomSeed() {
167 return absl::GetFlag(FLAGS_cp_random_seed) == -1
168 ? absl::Uniform<int64_t>(absl::BitGen(), 0, kint64max)
169 : absl::GetFlag(FLAGS_cp_random_seed);
170}

1067 // All factories (MakeXXX methods) encapsulate creation of objects
1068 // through RevAlloc(). Hence, the Solver used for allocating the
1069 // returned object will retain ownership of the allocated memory.
1070 // Destructors are called upon backtrack, or when the Solver is
1071 // itself destructed.

1210 template <typename F>
1211 Constraint* MakeLightElement(F values, IntVar* const var, IntVar* const index,
1212 std::function<bool()> deep_serialize = nullptr) {
1213 return RevAlloc(new LightIntFunctionElementCt<F>(
1214 this, var, index, std::move(values), std::move(deep_serialize)));
1215 }
1216
1223 template <typename F>
1224 Constraint* MakeLightElement(F values, IntVar* const var,
1225 IntVar* const index1, IntVar* const index2,
1226 std::function<bool()> deep_serialize = nullptr) {
1227 return RevAlloc(new LightIntIntFunctionElementCt<F>(
1228 this, var, index1, index2, std::move(values),
1229 std::move(deep_serialize)));
1230 }

2939 template <class T>
2940 void SaveAndSetValue(T* adr, T val) {
2941 if (*adr != val) {
2942 InternalSaveValue(adr);
2943 *adr = val;
2944 }
2945 }

2948 template <class T>
2949 void SaveAndAdd(T* adr, T val) {
2950 if (val != 0) {
2951 InternalSaveValue(adr);
2952 (*adr) += val;
2953 }
2954 }

3893template <class T>
3894class Rev {
3895 public:
3896 explicit Rev(const T& val) : stamp_(0), value_(val) {}
3897
3898 const T& Value() const { return value_; }
3899
3900 void SetValue(Solver* const s, const T& val) {
3901 if (val != value_) {
3902 if (stamp_ < s->stamp()) {
3903 s->SaveValue(&value_);
3904 stamp_ = s->stamp();
3905 }
3906 value_ = val;
3907 }
3908 }
3909
3910 private:
3911 uint64_t stamp_;
3912 T value_;
3913};
3914
3916template <class T>
3917class NumericalRev : public Rev<T> {
3918 public:
3919 explicit NumericalRev(const T& val) : Rev<T>(val) {}
3920
3921 void Add(Solver* const s, const T& to_add) {
3922 this->SetValue(s, this->Value() + to_add);
3923 }
3924
3925 void Incr(Solver* const s) { Add(s, 1); }
3926
3927 void Decr(Solver* const s) { Add(s, -1); }
3928};
3929
3935template <class T>
3936class RevArray {
3937 public:
3938 RevArray(int size, const T& val)
3939 : stamps_(new uint64_t[size]), values_(new T[size]), size_(size) {
3940 for (int i = 0; i < size; ++i) {
3941 stamps_[i] = 0;
3942 values_[i] = val;
3943 }
3944 }
3945
3946 ~RevArray() {}
3947
3948 int64_t size() const { return size_; }
3949
3950 const T& Value(int index) const { return values_[index]; }
3951
3952#if !defined(SWIG)
3953 const T& operator[](int index) const { return values_[index]; }
3954#endif
3955
3956 void SetValue(Solver* const s, int index, const T& val) {
3957 DCHECK_LT(index, size_);
3958 if (val != values_[index]) {
3959 if (stamps_[index] < s->stamp()) {
3960 s->SaveValue(&values_[index]);
3961 stamps_[index] = s->stamp();
3962 }
3963 values_[index] = val;
3964 }
3965 }
3966
3967 private:
3968 std::unique_ptr<uint64_t[]> stamps_;
3969 std::unique_ptr<T[]> values_;
3970 const int size_;
3971};
3972
3974template <class T>
3975class NumericalRevArray : public RevArray<T> {
3976 public:
3977 NumericalRevArray(int size, const T& val) : RevArray<T>(size, val) {}
3978
3979 void Add(Solver* const s, int index, const T& to_add) {
3980 this->SetValue(s, index, this->Value(index) + to_add);
3981 }
3982
3983 void Incr(Solver* const s, int index) { Add(s, index, 1); }
3984
3985 void Decr(Solver* const s, int index) { Add(s, index, -1); }
3986};

4093#ifndef SWIG
4100class InitAndGetValues {
4101 public:
4102 explicit InitAndGetValues(IntVarIterator* it)
4103 : it_(it), begin_was_called_(false) {
4104 it_->Init();
4105 }
4106 struct Iterator;
4107
4108 Iterator begin() {
4109 if (DEBUG_MODE) {
4110 DCHECK(!begin_was_called_);
4111 begin_was_called_ = true;
4112 }
4113 return Iterator::Begin(it_);
4114 }
4115 Iterator end() { return Iterator::End(it_); }
4116
4117 struct Iterator {
4119 static Iterator Begin(IntVarIterator* it) {
4120 return Iterator(it, /*is_end=*/false);
4121 }
4122 static Iterator End(IntVarIterator* it) {
4123 return Iterator(it, /*is_end=*/true);
4124 }
4125
4126 int64_t operator*() const {
4127 DCHECK(it_->Ok());
4128 return it_->Value();
4129 }
4130 Iterator& operator++() {
4131 DCHECK(it_->Ok());
4132 it_->Next();
4133 return *this;
4134 }
4135 bool operator!=(const Iterator& other) const {
4136 DCHECK(other.it_ == it_);
4137 DCHECK(other.is_end_);
4138 return it_->Ok();
4139 }
4140
4141 private:
4142 Iterator(IntVarIterator* it, bool is_end) : it_(it), is_end_(is_end) {}
4143
4144 IntVarIterator* const it_;
4145 const bool is_end_;
4146 };
4147
4148 private:
4149 IntVarIterator* const it_;
4150 bool begin_was_called_;
4151};
4152#endif // SWIG

4362// Base objective monitor class. All metaheuristics derive from this.
4363class ObjectiveMonitor : public SearchMonitor {
4364 public:
4365 ObjectiveMonitor(Solver* solver, const std::vector<bool>& maximize,
4366 std::vector<IntVar*> vars, std::vector<int64_t> steps);
4367 ~ObjectiveMonitor() override {}
4368#ifndef SWIG
4369 ObjectiveMonitor(const ObjectiveMonitor&) = delete;
4370 ObjectiveMonitor& operator=(const ObjectiveMonitor&) = delete;
4371#endif // SWIG
4372 IntVar* ObjectiveVar(int index) const { return objective_vars_[index]; }
4373 IntVar* MinimizationVar(int index) const { return minimization_vars_[index]; }
4374 int64_t Step(int index) const { return steps_[index]; }
4375 bool Maximize(int index) const {
4376 return ObjectiveVar(index) != MinimizationVar(index);
4377 }
4378 int64_t BestValue(int index) const {
4379 return Maximize(index) ? CapOpp(BestInternalValue(index))
4380 : BestInternalValue(index);
4381 }
4382 int Size() const { return objective_vars_.size(); }
4383 void EnterSearch() override;
4384 bool AtSolution() override;
4385 void Accept(ModelVisitor* visitor) const override;
4386
4387 protected:
4388 const std::vector<IntVar*>& objective_vars() const { return objective_vars_; }
4389 const std::vector<IntVar*>& minimization_vars() const {
4390 return minimization_vars_;
4391 }
4392 int64_t BestInternalValue(int index) const { return best_values_[index]; }
4393 int64_t CurrentInternalValue(int index) const {
4394 return current_values_[index];
4395 }
4396 void SetCurrentInternalValue(int index, int64_t value) {
4397 current_values_[index] = value;
4398 }
4399 template <typename T>
4400 void MakeMinimizationVarsLessOrEqualWithSteps(const T& upper_bounds) {
4401 if (Size() == 1) {
4402 MinimizationVar(0)->SetMax(CapSub(upper_bounds(0), Step(0)));
4403 } else {
4404 Solver* const solver = this->solver();
4405 for (int i = 0; i < Size(); ++i) {
4406 upper_bounds_[i] = solver->MakeIntConst(upper_bounds(i));
4407 }
4408 solver->AddConstraint(solver->MakeLexicalLessOrEqualWithOffsets(
4409 minimization_vars_, upper_bounds_, steps_));
4410 }
4411 }
4412 template <typename T>
4413 IntVar* MakeMinimizationVarsLessOrEqualWithStepsStatus(
4414 const T& upper_bounds) {
4415 Solver* const solver = this->solver();
4416 IntVar* status = solver->MakeBoolVar();
4417 if (Size() == 1) {
4418 solver->AddConstraint(solver->MakeIsLessOrEqualCstCt(
4419 MinimizationVar(0), CapSub(upper_bounds(0), Step(0)), status));
4420 } else {
4421 for (int i = 0; i < Size(); ++i) {
4422 upper_bounds_[i] = solver->MakeIntConst(upper_bounds(i));
4423 }
4424 solver->AddConstraint(solver->MakeIsLexicalLessOrEqualWithOffsetsCt(
4425 minimization_vars_, upper_bounds_, steps_, status));
4426 }
4427 return status;
4428 }
4429 bool CurrentInternalValuesAreConstraining() const;
4430
4431 bool found_initial_solution_;
4432
4433 private:
4434 friend class Solver;
4435 const std::vector<IntVar*> objective_vars_;
4436 std::vector<IntVar*> minimization_vars_;
4437 std::vector<IntVar*> upper_bounds_;
4438 std::vector<int64_t> steps_;
4439 std::vector<int64_t> best_values_;
4440 std::vector<int64_t> current_values_;
4441};

4585
4586// Limit based on the improvement rate of 'objective_var' or a lexicographic
4587// objective composed of 'objective_vars'.
4588// This limit proceeds in two stages:
4589// 1) During the phase of the search in which the objective is strictly
4590// improving, a threshold value is computed as the minimum improvement rate of
4591// the objective, based on the 'improvement_rate_coefficient' and
4592// 'improvement_rate_solutions_distance' parameters.
4593// 2) Then, if the search continues beyond this phase of strict improvement, the
4594// limit stops the search when the improvement rate of the objective gets below
4595// this threshold value.
4596class ImprovementSearchLimit : public SearchLimit {
4597 public:
4598 ImprovementSearchLimit(Solver* solver, IntVar* objective_var, bool maximize,
4599 double objective_scaling_factor,
4600 double objective_offset,
4601 double improvement_rate_coefficient,
4602 int improvement_rate_solutions_distance);
4603 ImprovementSearchLimit(Solver* solver, std::vector<IntVar*> objective_vars,
4604 std::vector<bool> maximize,
4605 std::vector<double> objective_scaling_factors,
4606 std::vector<double> objective_offsets,
4607 double improvement_rate_coefficient,
4608 int improvement_rate_solutions_distance);
4609 ~ImprovementSearchLimit() override;
4610 void Copy(const SearchLimit* limit) override;
4611 SearchLimit* MakeClone() const override;
4612 bool CheckWithOffset(absl::Duration offset) override;
4613 bool AtSolution() override;
4614 void Init() override;
4615 void Install() override;
4616
4617 private:
4618 std::vector<IntVar*> objective_vars_;
4619 std::vector<bool> maximize_;
4620 std::vector<double> objective_scaling_factors_;
4621 std::vector<double> objective_offsets_;
4622 double improvement_rate_coefficient_;
4623 int improvement_rate_solutions_distance_;
4624
4625 std::vector<double> best_objectives_;
4626 // clang-format off
4627 std::vector<std::deque<std::pair<double, int64_t> > > improvements_;
4628 // clang-format on
4629 std::vector<double> thresholds_;
4630 bool objective_updated_;
4631 bool gradient_stage_;
4632};

4899class IntVarElement : public AssignmentElement {
4900 public:
4901 IntVarElement();
4902 explicit IntVarElement(IntVar* var);
4903 void Reset(IntVar* var);
4904 IntVarElement* Clone();
4905 void Copy(const IntVarElement& element);
4906 IntVar* Var() const { return var_; }
4907 void Store() {
4908 min_ = var_->Min();
4909 max_ = var_->Max();
4910 }
4911 void Restore() {
4912 if (var_ != nullptr) {
4913 var_->SetRange(min_, max_);
4914 }
4915 }
4916 void LoadFromProto(const IntVarAssignment& int_var_assignment_proto);
4917 void WriteToProto(IntVarAssignment* int_var_assignment_proto) const;
4918
4919 int64_t Min() const { return min_; }
4920 void SetMin(int64_t m) { min_ = m; }
4921 int64_t Max() const { return max_; }
4922 void SetMax(int64_t m) { max_ = m; }
4923 int64_t Value() const {
4924 DCHECK_EQ(min_, max_);
4925 // Get the value from an unbound int var assignment element.
4926 return min_;
4927 }
4928 bool Bound() const { return (max_ == min_); }
4929 void SetRange(int64_t l, int64_t u) {
4930 min_ = l;
4931 max_ = u;
4932 }
4933 void SetValue(int64_t v) {
4934 min_ = v;
4935 max_ = v;
4936 }
4937 std::string DebugString() const;
4938
4939 bool operator==(const IntVarElement& element) const;
4940 bool operator!=(const IntVarElement& element) const {
4941 return !(*this == element);
4942 }
4943
4944 private:
4945 IntVar* var_;
4946 int64_t min_;
4947 int64_t max_;
4948};

4950class IntervalVarElement : public AssignmentElement {
4951 public:
4952 IntervalVarElement();
4953 explicit IntervalVarElement(IntervalVar* var);
4954 void Reset(IntervalVar* var);
4955 IntervalVarElement* Clone();

4957 IntervalVar* Var() const { return var_; }
4958 void Store();
4959 void Restore();
4960 void LoadFromProto(
4961 const IntervalVarAssignment& interval_var_assignment_proto);
4962 void WriteToProto(IntervalVarAssignment* interval_var_assignment_proto) const;
4963
4964 int64_t StartMin() const { return start_min_; }
4965 int64_t StartMax() const { return start_max_; }
4966 int64_t StartValue() const {
4967 CHECK_EQ(start_max_, start_min_);
4968 return start_max_;
4969 }
4970 int64_t DurationMin() const { return duration_min_; }
4971 int64_t DurationMax() const { return duration_max_; }
4972 int64_t DurationValue() const {
4973 CHECK_EQ(duration_max_, duration_min_);
4974 return duration_max_;
4975 }
4976 int64_t EndMin() const { return end_min_; }
4977 int64_t EndMax() const { return end_max_; }
4978 int64_t EndValue() const {
4979 CHECK_EQ(end_max_, end_min_);
4980 return end_max_;
4981 }
4982 int64_t PerformedMin() const { return performed_min_; }
4983 int64_t PerformedMax() const { return performed_max_; }
4984 int64_t PerformedValue() const {
4985 CHECK_EQ(performed_max_, performed_min_);
4986 return performed_max_;
4987 }
4988 void SetStartMin(int64_t m) { start_min_ = m; }
4989 void SetStartMax(int64_t m) { start_max_ = m; }
4990 void SetStartRange(int64_t mi, int64_t ma) {
4991 start_min_ = mi;
4992 start_max_ = ma;
4993 }
4994 void SetStartValue(int64_t v) {
4995 start_min_ = v;
4996 start_max_ = v;
4997 }
4998 void SetDurationMin(int64_t m) { duration_min_ = m; }
4999 void SetDurationMax(int64_t m) { duration_max_ = m; }
5000 void SetDurationRange(int64_t mi, int64_t ma) {
5001 duration_min_ = mi;
5002 duration_max_ = ma;
5003 }
5004 void SetDurationValue(int64_t v) {
5005 duration_min_ = v;
5006 duration_max_ = v;
5007 }
5008 void SetEndMin(int64_t m) { end_min_ = m; }
5009 void SetEndMax(int64_t m) { end_max_ = m; }
5010 void SetEndRange(int64_t mi, int64_t ma) {
5011 end_min_ = mi;
5012 end_max_ = ma;
5013 }
5014 void SetEndValue(int64_t v) {
5015 end_min_ = v;
5016 end_max_ = v;
5017 }
5018 void SetPerformedMin(int64_t m) { performed_min_ = m; }
5019 void SetPerformedMax(int64_t m) { performed_max_ = m; }
5020 void SetPerformedRange(int64_t mi, int64_t ma) {
5021 performed_min_ = mi;
5022 performed_max_ = ma;
5023 }
5024 void SetPerformedValue(int64_t v) {
5025 performed_min_ = v;
5026 performed_max_ = v;
5027 }
5028 bool Bound() const {
5029 return (start_min_ == start_max_ && duration_min_ == duration_max_ &&
5030 end_min_ == end_max_ && performed_min_ == performed_max_);
5031 }
5032 std::string DebugString() const;
5033 bool operator==(const IntervalVarElement& element) const;
5034 bool operator!=(const IntervalVarElement& element) const {
5035 return !(*this == element);
5036 }
5037
5038 private:
5039 int64_t start_min_;
5040 int64_t start_max_;
5041 int64_t duration_min_;
5042 int64_t duration_max_;
5043 int64_t end_min_;
5044 int64_t end_max_;
5045 int64_t performed_min_;
5046 int64_t performed_max_;
5047 IntervalVar* var_;
5048};

5105
5106template <class V, class E>
5107class AssignmentContainer {
5108 public:
5109 AssignmentContainer() {}
5110 E* Add(V* var) {
5111 CHECK(var != nullptr);
5112 int index = -1;
5113 if (!Find(var, &index)) {
5114 return FastAdd(var);
5115 } else {
5116 return &elements_[index];
5117 }
5118 }
5120 E* FastAdd(V* var) {
5121 DCHECK(var != nullptr);
5122 elements_.emplace_back(var);
5123 return &elements_.back();
5124 }
5127 E* AddAtPosition(V* var, int position) {
5128 elements_[position].Reset(var);
5129 return &elements_[position];
5130 }
5131 void Clear() {
5132 elements_.clear();
5133 if (!elements_map_.empty()) {
5134 elements_map_.clear();
5135 }
5136 }
5139 void Resize(size_t size) { elements_.resize(size); }
5140 bool Empty() const { return elements_.empty(); }
5143 void CopyIntersection(const AssignmentContainer<V, E>& container) {
5144 for (int i = 0; i < container.elements_.size(); ++i) {
5145 const E& element = container.elements_[i];
5146 const V* const var = element.Var();
5147 int index = -1;
5148 if (i < elements_.size() && elements_[i].Var() == var) {
5149 index = i;
5150 } else if (!Find(var, &index)) {
5151 continue;
5152 }
5153 DCHECK_GE(index, 0);
5154 E* const local_element = &elements_[index];
5155 local_element->Copy(element);
5156 if (element.Activated()) {
5157 local_element->Activate();
5158 } else {
5159 local_element->Deactivate();
5160 }
5161 }
5162 }
5165 void Copy(const AssignmentContainer<V, E>& container) {
5166 Clear();
5167 for (int i = 0; i < container.elements_.size(); ++i) {
5168 const E& element = container.elements_[i];
5169 FastAdd(element.Var())->Copy(element);
5170 }
5171 }
5172 bool Contains(const V* const var) const {
5173 int index;
5174 return Find(var, &index);
5175 }
5176 E* MutableElement(const V* const var) {
5177 E* const element = MutableElementOrNull(var);
5178 DCHECK(element != nullptr)
5179 << "Unknown variable " << var->DebugString() << " in solution";
5180 return element;
5181 }
5182 E* MutableElementOrNull(const V* const var) {
5183 int index = -1;
5184 if (Find(var, &index)) {
5185 return MutableElement(index);
5186 }
5187 return nullptr;
5188 }
5189 const E& Element(const V* const var) const {
5190 const E* const element = ElementPtrOrNull(var);
5191 DCHECK(element != nullptr)
5192 << "Unknown variable " << var->DebugString() << " in solution";
5193 return *element;
5194 }
5195 const E* ElementPtrOrNull(const V* const var) const {
5196 int index = -1;
5197 if (Find(var, &index)) {
5198 return &Element(index);
5199 }
5200 return nullptr;
5201 }
5202 const std::vector<E>& elements() const { return elements_; }
5203 E* MutableElement(int index) { return &elements_[index]; }
5204 const E& Element(int index) const { return elements_[index]; }
5205 int Size() const { return elements_.size(); }
5206 void Store() {
5207 for (E& element : elements_) {
5208 element.Store();
5209 }
5210 }
5211 void Restore() {
5212 for (E& element : elements_) {
5213 if (element.Activated()) {
5214 element.Restore();
5215 }
5216 }
5217 }
5218 bool AreAllElementsBound() const {
5219 for (const E& element : elements_) {
5220 if (!element.Bound()) return false;
5221 }
5222 return true;
5223 }
5224
5228 bool operator==(const AssignmentContainer<V, E>& container) const {
5230 if (Size() != container.Size()) {
5231 return false;
5232 }
5234 EnsureMapIsUpToDate();
5238 for (const E& element : container.elements_) {
5239 const int position =
5240 gtl::FindWithDefault(elements_map_, element.Var(), -1);
5241 if (position < 0 || elements_[position] != element) {
5242 return false;
5243 }
5244 }
5245 return true;
5246 }
5247 bool operator!=(const AssignmentContainer<V, E>& container) const {
5248 return !(*this == container);
5249 }
5250
5251 private:
5252 void EnsureMapIsUpToDate() const {
5253 absl::flat_hash_map<const V*, int>* map =
5254 const_cast<absl::flat_hash_map<const V*, int>*>(&elements_map_);
5255 for (int i = map->size(); i < elements_.size(); ++i) {
5256 (*map)[elements_[i].Var()] = i;
5257 }
5258 }
5259 bool Find(const V* const var, int* index) const {
5261 const size_t kMaxSizeForLinearAccess = 11;
5262 if (Size() <= kMaxSizeForLinearAccess) {
5266 for (int i = 0; i < elements_.size(); ++i) {
5267 if (var == elements_[i].Var()) {
5268 *index = i;
5269 return true;
5270 }
5271 }
5272 return false;
5273 } else {
5274 EnsureMapIsUpToDate();
5275 DCHECK_EQ(elements_map_.size(), elements_.size());
5276 return gtl::FindCopy(elements_map_, var, index);
5277 }
5278 }
5279
5280 std::vector<E> elements_;
5281 absl::flat_hash_map<const V*, int> elements_map_;
5282};
